We are given an root node of the binary search tree and our job is to return k th smallest element.

In BST we know that the tree is always balanced so we can do in order traversal of the tree and store the elements in a array/list and return k-1th  element.

1. Create an empty list.

2. Do inorder traversal:
   - Visit left subtree.
   - Add current node value.
   - Visit right subtree.

3. After traversal, the list contains BST values in sorted order.

4. Return list.get(k - 1).

class solution{

public ArrayList<Integer> inOrder(TreeNode arr, ArrayList<Integer> arr)
{
if(root == null) return arr;

inOrder(root.left, arr);
arr.add(root.val);
inOrder(root.right, arr);

return arr;
}

public int kthSmallest(TreeNode root, int k)
{

 ArrayList<Integer> nums = inOrder(root, new ArrayList<Integer>());
 return nums.get(k-1);
 }
 }
